5
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:55.820
Kostadis Roussos: Suggesting that the Waters Temple's profits had orchestrated the entire affair as a calculated win-win, either eliminating the party or bankrupt the Fire Temple in the process.

6
00:00:55.820 --> 00:01:09.570
Kostadis Roussos: The warlock also carried a heavy gold amulet bearing the eight-pointed symbol of the Fire Temple, a potion of fire resistance he had never managed to reach for, a masterwork, a whip of alchemically treated leather, and a heavy iron chain stamped with a mask.

7
00:01:09.570 --> 00:01:11.280
Kostadis Roussos: of Knobbs River Pirates.

8
00:01:12.230 --> 00:01:15.860
Kostadis Roussos: The party brought their findings to ROMAG, etc. Alright.

9
00:01:16.050 --> 00:01:26.260
Kostadis Roussos: When Xenia pressed harsh on his feelings about Romag's passive erosion-like philosophy of leadership, Harp made it clear to hide his ambition. If a position of leadership were to suddenly open itself, he would absolutely consider himself worthy.

10
00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:43.900
Kostadis Roussos: The party recognized the single for what it was. Harch wanted Romag removed, and he wanted them to do it. A bold and dangerous plan crystallized. Assassinate Romag, install Harch as the Earth Temple's new leader, and engineer a three-way war between the Earth, Fire, and Water Temples to destroy all three factions from within.

11
00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:48.039
Kostadis Roussos: They quietly agreed that the time for subtlety was nearly over, but not quite yet.

12
00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:57.210
Kostadis Roussos: Rather than alerting Harch to their intentions, the party closed to execute a surgical coup without his foreknowledge, planning to present him with power as a fait accompli.

13
00:01:57.210 --> 00:02:12.179
Kostadis Roussos: They enlisted Dren, the leader of the Crimson Guards, to arrange a morning meeting with Romag, ensuring the High Priest would be present and off guard. Dren, visibly impressed by the party's victory over the Chimera, agreed without hesitation, and returned with confirmation that Romag was looking forward to the meeting.

14
00:02:12.310 --> 00:02:32.099
Kostadis Roussos: The party slipped through a secret passage into the earth temple's inner sanctum, emerging into Romag's sleeping chamber, a room decorated with earthen motifs, its floor covered in dirt, a small altar in the corner, and dust scattered with personal notes. Sequoia crept behind a curtain, separating the chamber from the adjoining room, where he could hear a Romag lecturing heart.

15
00:02:32.100 --> 00:02:34.660
Kostadis Roussos: On the slow, erosive power of dust.

16
00:02:34.660 --> 00:02:47.480
Kostadis Roussos: While Harch barely concealed his disdain behind carefully chosen words of agreement, Sakai also noticed with some urgency that the door to the south stood open. If RogMag cried out, guards would come flooding in, and the entire operation would unravel.

17
00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:52.679
Kostadis Roussos: The party moved swiftly. Zephter invoked a subtle but powerful magic, causing the doors of…

18
00:02:52.810 --> 00:03:09.990
Kostadis Roussos: Romag's chamber to slam shut with a resonant bang, sealing the chamber from the outside world. Harch instantly understood what was happening, placed his weapons on the ground, and stepped aside. Romag turned his face, shifting from confusion to horror. Azini rushed him with a flurry of precise, devastating strikes.

19
00:03:09.990 --> 00:03:20.259
Kostadis Roussos: Followed by Sequoia landing blow after blow on the stunned priest. Colmarin nearly invoked the name of his holy patron before catching himself in the most spectacularly ill-timed moment imaginable.

20
00:03:20.260 --> 00:03:44.249
Kostadis Roussos: Instead, channeled a wave of necrotic power that caused Romag to wither and collapse dead upon the floor. Harch did not hesitate. He plunged his hands into Romag's blood, covered them in blood, and marched into the main chamber of the Earth Temple, holding Romag's sacred bezments aloft. He declared himself supreme prophet, announcing that the era of passive resignation was over, and that the destructive power of Earth would now be unleashed upon their enemies.

21
00:03:44.380 --> 00:03:57.900
Kostadis Roussos: The Gather Cultist erupted in cheers, and Harch introduced the party to his troops as the Obsidian Edge, his personal vanguard, the sharpest stone in the deep earth, cutting through fire and water from the shadows before anyone felt the quake.

